'''Altena''' or '''Van Altena''' is a [[Dutch language|Dutch]] [[toponymic surname]].<ref>[http://www.cbgfamilienamen.nl/nfb/detail_naam.php?gba_lcnaam=altena&gba_naam=Altena&nfd_naam=Altena&operator=bw&taal= Altena] at the Database of Surnames in The Netherlands.</ref> [[Altena (disambiguation)|Altena]] is the name of at least six locations in the Low Countries, as well as several in neighboring Germany. At least one family traces the name back to the [[Land van Altena]], now in [[North Brabant]]. People with the name include:
*[[Bob Altena]] (born 1986), Dutch decathlete *[[Ernst van Altena]] (1933–1999), Dutch poet, writer and translator *[[Klaus Altena]] (born 1962), German rower *[[Maarten Altena]] (born 1943), Dutch composer *[[Marius van Altena]] (born 1938), Dutch tenor
==See also== *[[2370 van Altena]], main belt asteroid named after Willem van Altena, Dutch-born American astronomer *[[De Borchgrave d'Altena]], noble family from 's-Hertogenbosch *[[Calliostoma altena]], sea snail named after Dutch curator Carel O. van Regteren Altena (1907-1976)
