[[File:Goats in landscape management at German Highway A 59. Spielvogel 2013.jpg|thumb|right|Goats managing the landscape alongside German autobahn [[Bundesautobahn 59|A59]].]] '''Goat groundskeeping''' is the use of [[goat]]s to eat vegetation as a form of [[landscape maintenance]] or [[conservation grazing]]. As goats are [[herd animal]]s, several goats are usually used together and so companies such as [http://www.californiagrazing.com/ California Grazing], [http://www.eco-goats.com/ Eco-Goats] and [[Rent A Goat]] exist to rent such herds out, as needed.<ref name=MF/> This may be expensive and their smell may be a nuisance.<ref name=BBC/>
==Landscape maintenance==
{{Empty section|date=August 2016}}
==Targeted grazing== Chattannooga, TN and Spartanburg, SC have used goats to control kudzu, an invasive plant species prevalent in the southeastern United States.<ref name=NYT/>
