{{Expand Swedish|topic=structure|date=August 2010|Sundsby}} {{Infobox building | name = Sundsby | native_name = | native_name_lang = | former_names = | alternate_names = | image = | image_alt = | caption = | map_type = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location in [[Sweden]] | altitude = | building_type = | architectural_style = | structural_system = | cost = | ren_cost = | client = | owner = | current_tenants = | landlord = | location = [[Bohuslän]] | address = | location_town = | location_country = {{flag|Sweden}} | coordinates = {{coord|58|04|13|N|11|41|20|E|region:SE_type:landmark|display=title,inline}} | start_date = | completion_date = | inauguration_date = | renovation_date = | demolition_date = | destruction_date = | height = | diameter = | antenna_spire = | roof = | top_floor = | other_dimensions = | floor_count = | floor_area = | seating_type = | seating_capacity = | elevator_count = | main_contractor = | architect = | architecture_firm = | structural_engineer = | services_engineer = | civil_engineer = | other_designers = | quantity_surveyor = | awards = | ren_architect = | ren_firm = | ren_str_engineer = | ren_serv_engineer = | ren_civ_engineer = | ren_oth_designers = | ren_qty_surveyor = | ren_awards = | url = | references = }}
[[File:Sundsby säteri04.jpg|thumb|250 px|Sundsby säteri]] [[File:Sundsby Säteri, huvudbyggnad och sidobyggnader.jpg|thumb|250 px|Sundsby säteri]]
'''Sundsby''' is a protected area located on the island of Mjörn in [[Tjörn Municipality]], [[Bohuslän]], [[Sweden]]. This is the site of Sundsby Manor (''Sundsby säteri''). <ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.lansstyrelsen.se/vastragotaland/Sv/djur-och-natur/skyddad-natur/naturreservat/lanets-naturreservat/tjorn/sundsby/Pages/index.aspx |title=Sundsby|publisher =vastragotaland/Sv |accessdate= May 1, 2018}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url = http://runeberg.org/hgsl/6/0368.html|title=Sundsby Sundsby, Walla socken af Göteborgs och Bohus län|publisher =Historiskt-geografiskt och statistiskt lexikon öfver Sverige|accessdate= May 1, 2018}}</ref>
Sundsby dates to the Middle Ages and was first mentioned during 1388 by Bishop [[Eysteinn Erlendsson]], Bishop of the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Nidaros| Archdiocese of Nidaros]]. In the second half of the 16th century, it came under the control of Laurits Olofsson Green (ca.1505-1581). His son Anders Lauritsson Green (ca. 1550-1614), who became Norwegian Chancellor, inherited Sundsby and significantly expanded the estate. After he died childless, Sundsby was inherited by his great niece, [[Margareta Huitfeldt]] in 1625. She and her husband, Thomas Dyre, further expanded the estate through purchase of adjacent property. Huitfeldt built an extensive estate complex around the fjords in central Bohuslän. <ref>{{cite web|url = http://runeberg.org/rosenberg/2/0726.html|title=Sundsby i Göteborgs och Bohus län|publisher =Geografiskt-statistiskt handlexikon öfver Sverige |author=Carl Martin Rosenberg|accessdate= May 1, 2018}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.tjsf.org/slakter/green.htm |title= Släkten Green av Sundsby och Margareta Huitfeldt|publisher = tjsf.org/ |author= Anders Ryberg |accessdate= May 1, 2018}}</ref>
The older buildings burned down in 1720 and new buildings were built circa 1763. An extensive remodel was made in the 1890s. In the 1930s, the barn was refurbished and during the 1940s, the main building's interior was rebuilt. Tjörn municipality bought Sundsby in 2003. Since 2006, the area has been accessible to the public. Sundsby Säteri features an exhibition about Margareta Huitfeldt and access to guided tours, together with a café, restaurant, shop and bakery. The estate contains a garden surrounded by a hilly, wooded landscape edged by bays. The area is part of the [[European Union]] [[Special Area of Conservation]]. <ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.tjorn.se/kulturturismfritid/turismochsevardheter/sevardheterochbesoksmal/sundsbysateri.4.24c2bb5114a2cdba7ad6570.html |title= Välkommen till Sundsby|publisher =. Tjörn Kommun |accessdate= May 1, 2018}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.vastsverige.com/en/sodra-bohuslan/produkter/sundsby-sateri/|title= Sundsby Manor/Sundsby Säteri |publisher = vastsverige.com |accessdate= May 1, 2018}}</ref>
